# React UI Patterns

- **Component style**
  - Use functional components with explicit `Props` types; prefer named exports for shared primitives, default exports for pages.
  - Mark interactive client components with `"use client";` at the top; keep server components free of browser-only APIs.

- **Composition**
  - Reuse existing primitives like `Button`, `Card`, `SectionLayout`, and form controls instead of ad-hoc markup.
  - Keep page components (`app/**/page.tsx`) focused on layout and composition; push stateful logic into hooks (e.g. `useTweetList`).

- **State & hooks**
  - Co-locate UI state and side-effects in hooks under `hooks/**` and keep components mostly declarative.
  - Derive simple values (e.g. formatted timestamps, follower text) inline in components rather than storing them in state.

- **Accessibility & semantics**
  - Use semantic HTML elements (`<main>`, `<section>`, `<button>`, `<label>`, `aria-*`) consistent with existing components.
  - When using icon-only or icon-leading buttons, ensure labels remain readable and focus styles are preserved.

- **Styling**
  - Use Tailwind utility classes and design tokens (`bg-background`, `text-muted`, radius tokens) consistent with `app/globals.css`.
  - Prefer `cn()` for conditional classes, particularly when toggling disabled/active states.
